## Summary of Key Causes of East Germany’s Fall

| Cause Category          | Description                                                                                 | Impact                                                                                   |
|------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Economic Weakness       | Command economy, reparations, debt, brain drain, lack of innovation                        | Economic stagnation, shortages, declining productivity, loss of skilled labor             |
| Political Repression   | SED dictatorship, Stasi surveillance, suppression of dissent                               | Public discontent, withdrawal into private life, eventual protest movements               |
| Cultural Exposure      | Access to West German media and consumer culture                                          | Increased dissatisfaction and desire for Western freedoms                               |
| Soviet Influence       | Dependence on USSR, Soviet economic decline, Gorbachev’s reforms                          | Loss of external support, lack of intervention during protests                           |
| Emigration and Border  | Mass emigration, Berlin Wall as a symbol of division, eventual fall of the Wall           | Loss of population and legitimacy, collapse of physical barrier to freedom               |

